# Dependency Fidelity Manifest

List every external dependency with its tier, implementation, and declared gaps.
Specifier and QA: do not write or accept scenarios that rest on a declared gap.

Tier definitions:
- Tier 0 — the system itself: always runs real, as shipped. Never substituted.
- Tier 1 — owned infrastructure: runs the real engine locally (e.g. Postgres in Docker).
- Tier 2 — emulated dependency: stateful, protocol-level emulation. Declare what the emulator does not implement.
- Tier 3 — external domain: third-party APIs or other teams' services. Always wire-level stubbed. Declare contract reference and gaps.

## Dependencies

(none — add entries as: `- <name>: tier <N>; <implementation>; gaps: <description or none>`)
